title: Scuba Map
name: Scuba Map
description:
A Map by Mysticgringo

Places in the world I have Scuba'd.

properties.name: Beqa Island, Fiji. 2005
properties.description: Posted by MysticgringoThis is where I dove in September 2005, with my folks. The place we stayed was Kulu Bay Resort, and their dive operation was... relaxed. The diving was awesome though, probably some of the best in the world.

properties.name: Caye Caulker, Belize. 2006
properties.description: Posted by MysticgringoCaye Caulker was a cool town. I dove with Frenchies dive shop... which was very chill, people were very cool, and it was well run.

properties.name: Costa Rica, 2006
properties.description: Posted by MysticgringoI forget the name of this little town, in Costa Rica where I did my open water course. I dove alot before that... but was never certified until this point. The diving here was un-spectacular.

properties.name: Curacao, Netherlands, Antilles. 2006.
properties.description: Posted by MysticgringoSpent a week in October diving out of Sunset Waters. Decent diving, and good resort.

properties.name: Flinders Reef, Australia. Pree-2k
properties.description: Posted by MysticgringoThis is where I grew up diving. My parents taught me to do the scuba thing, and this reef spoiled me for the rest of my diving ever. Ofcourse, I remember the bizzare creatures, and fantastic colors of this new world... and no place I have dove since has come close to this. Some day, I will go back to here... and ruin my memories of how spectacular it was.

properties.name: Roatan, Honduras. 2005
properties.description: Posted by MysticgringoThis is Roatan, Honduras, where I dove for a week with my parents out of Anthony\'s Key Resort. This is probably one of the most efficient, and well run dive opperations I have seen.

properties.name: Tangalooma, Australia. Pre-2k
properties.description: Posted by MysticgringoThese wrecks were an awesome place to hangout at. Snorkling was great, diving was good... and the sandhills were fun.

properties.name: Turneffe Atol, Belize. 2006
properties.description: Posted by MysticgringoI dove for a week out of Blackbird Caye resort. Where we dove the famous Blue Hole, and other cool sites. Good diving, and great resort.

properties.name: Utila, Honduras. 2005
properties.description: Posted by MysticgringoThis is Utila Island, Honduras, where I dove May and August of 2005 with the Utila Dive Center. This is also where I took my PADI Advanced, and PADI Rescue Diver courses.
